### Proxy and Reflect

`Proxy` wraps an object and intercepts fundamental operations via **traps**. `Reflect` provides default implementations of those same operations — using it inside a trap ensures correct forwarding behavior.

**Key traps:**
- `get(target, prop, receiver)` — property access
- `set(target, prop, value, receiver)` — property assignment
- `has(target, prop)` — `in` operator
- `deleteProperty(target, prop)` — `delete` operator
- `apply(target, thisArg, args)` — function call
- `construct(target, args)` — `new` operator

```javascript
// Validation proxy
function createValidated(schema) {
  return new Proxy({}, {
    set(target, prop, value, receiver) {
      if (schema[prop] && !schema[prop](value)) {
        throw new TypeError(`Invalid value for ${prop}: ${value}`);
      }
      return Reflect.set(target, prop, value, receiver);
      // Reflect.set handles inherited setters, receiver correctly
    },
    get(target, prop, receiver) {
      return Reflect.get(target, prop, receiver);
    }
  });
}

const user = createValidated({
  age: v => typeof v === 'number' && v >= 0 && v <= 150
});
user.age = 25;   // OK
user.age = -1;   // TypeError: Invalid value for age: -1
user.name = 'Alice'; // OK — no schema rule
```

**Why Reflect alongside Proxy:**
- `Reflect.get(target, prop, receiver)` correctly handles inherited getters where `this` should be `receiver` (the proxy), not `target`. Using `target[prop]` directly breaks this.
- `Reflect` methods return the same values as the trap is expected to return (boolean for `set`, etc.), so they serve as safe defaults.

```javascript
// Logging proxy for any object
const logger = (obj) => new Proxy(obj, {
  get(target, prop, receiver) {
    console.log(`GET ${String(prop)}`);
    return Reflect.get(target, prop, receiver);
  },
  set(target, prop, value, receiver) {
    console.log(`SET ${String(prop)} = ${value}`);
    return Reflect.set(target, prop, value, receiver);
  }
});
```

**Common trap:** Forgetting `receiver` in `Reflect.get`/`Reflect.set` — this breaks classes that use getters/setters defined on a prototype.

**Частая ошибка:** Забывать `receiver` в `Reflect.get`/`Reflect.set` — это ломает классы, использующие геттеры/сеттеры на прототипе.

